15:59.900 --> 16:00.967
[Judy] First show me.

16:01.033 --> 16:03.333
Just show me. You already
have the flowers down here.

16:03.400 --> 16:04.533
-Yes.
-[Judy] As 190.

16:04.700 --> 16:05.867
You're getting credit for that.

16:05.934 --> 16:07.767
-So far, we're to 470.
-[Carlos] And...

16:07.834 --> 16:10.200
I'd like to see what you did to reserve--

16:10.266 --> 16:13.033
Where are the contracts
with the table companies,

16:13.100 --> 16:14.200
the chair companies?

16:14.266 --> 16:15.333
They are my tables.

16:15.400 --> 16:16.633
[Judy] Oh, then you're
not entitled to that.

16:16.700 --> 16:19.333
No, no, bah, okay.
Can I-- can I say something?

16:19.400 --> 16:20.567
Yeah.

16:20.934 --> 16:24.934
Okay, when she cancelled
it because for COVID, it wasn't...

16:25.000 --> 16:26.834
[Judy] No, she didn't cancel it
because of COVID.

16:26.900 --> 16:31.000
The contract that you rendered
was unenforceable by law.

16:31.066 --> 16:32.567
It was unenforceable.

16:32.800 --> 16:33.967
Based upon her figure,

16:34.033 --> 16:36.900
it was a little bit more than
four hours

16:36.967 --> 16:38.333
that you spent with her,

16:38.400 --> 16:40.900
but you're not entitled to
making a contract with yourself.

16:40.967 --> 16:43.533
I mean, if you engaged
in contract negotiations

16:43.600 --> 16:46.133
with other vendors for
chairs or anything else,

16:46.200 --> 16:48.300
I would consider that,
but so far, you didn't.

16:48.367 --> 16:50.400
So, the contract
was unenforceable.

16:50.467 --> 16:53.133
And based upon your own statement to her,

16:53.200 --> 16:55.233
the time that you spent
was four hours.

16:55.300 --> 16:58.900
You're entitled to that, at $70 an hour,
which is exactly what you earn,

16:58.967 --> 17:03.166
and the flowers that,
put together, were $190.

17:03.233 --> 17:07.433
So, that together is $470.

17:07.500 --> 17:12.500
And, therefore,
you should return to her $3,630.

17:12.567 --> 17:13.734
Um...

17:13.800 --> 17:15.633
-[Judy] "Um" is not an answer.
-No, no. [laughs]

17:15.700 --> 17:16.800
I want to know what else you did.

17:16.867 --> 17:18.400
If you did something else, tell me.

17:18.467 --> 17:21.967
We make sure
that tables and the layers

17:22.033 --> 17:25.266
that she wants for her table
and also...

17:25.333 --> 17:27.266
Those are your things,
you said to me.

17:27.333 --> 17:28.333
That's your property.

17:28.400 --> 17:31.934
But we then sell it to another person
because we already have...

17:32.000 --> 17:33.066
[Judy] You couldn't sell,
you couldn't sell it,

17:33.133 --> 17:36.800
you couldn't-- you couldn't
sell it or rent it to another person

17:36.867 --> 17:40.367
because everything else
was closed after March.

17:40.633 --> 17:41.900
Everything else was closed.

17:41.967 --> 17:43.667
You couldn't rent them
to anybody else.

17:43.734 --> 17:44.967
-[Carlos] Of course not.
-[Judy] Of course not.

17:45.033 --> 17:47.734
Okay.
The cancellation of these events

17:47.800 --> 17:50.333
wrought havoc
on the venue business

17:50.400 --> 17:53.300
for well over a year,
probably still is.

17:53.367 --> 17:55.900
As I said, you're entitled
to be compensated.

17:55.967 --> 17:59.967
And I certainly would not
give her back her $4,000

18:00.100 --> 18:03.533
because that would sort of be
like her missing a week's pay

18:03.600 --> 18:05.934
if they close the plant
where she was working,

18:06.000 --> 18:08.700
and she would say, well, I was here,
I'm ready to do my job.

18:08.767 --> 18:10.266
And the plant would say,
listen, this is COVID.

18:10.333 --> 18:12.300
But I actually
came to work every day.

18:12.367 --> 18:14.600
I drove there every day,
I did work from home,

18:14.667 --> 18:16.433
I expended time.

18:16.500 --> 18:18.934
She would want to be paid,
you're entitled to be paid.

18:19.000 --> 18:24.800
But by your own analysis, what
you're entitled to be paid was $370.

18:24.867 --> 18:28.734
And so, she gets her deposit back,
less that $370.

18:28.800 --> 18:30.400
-Thank you. We're finished.
-Thank you.

