18:36.834 --> 18:38.000
I think it was very fair.

18:38.066 --> 18:39.400
I don't think it's fair.

18:39.467 --> 18:43.834
Uh, everything with the COVID,
like our company,

18:43.900 --> 18:45.233
it was very difficult and--

18:45.300 --> 18:48.066
I tried.
I sent texts, I sent emails,

18:48.133 --> 18:50.166
um, I had a lawyer
send a demand letter

18:50.233 --> 18:51.834
to try and resolve it
before we got here,

18:51.900 --> 18:53.266
um, to no resolve.

18:53.500 --> 18:54.667
But I'm happy.

18:54.734 --> 18:58.767
To give back money right now
is very difficult for our company,

18:58.834 --> 19:00.066
and obviously myself.

19:00.133 --> 19:02.100
Time to live happily ever after now.

19:02.166 --> 19:05.100
I'm going to change
that contract to be more clear.

19:05.166 --> 19:08.233
So, although it wasn't my
best class in all of law school,

19:08.300 --> 19:10.000
one thing I do remember
from contracts

19:10.066 --> 19:12.633
is the importance
of a force majeure clause,

19:12.700 --> 19:15.700
where it allocates, uh,
the risk of loss

19:15.767 --> 19:19.834
if something unexpected happens
at no fault of either party.

19:19.900 --> 19:21.834
And in this case,
they really could have benefited

19:21.900 --> 19:25.467
from a clause such as that
because they could have stated

19:25.533 --> 19:28.033
who was going to pay,
what the refund was going to be,

19:28.100 --> 19:29.967
how much she was
compensated for time

19:30.033 --> 19:31.934
if the wedding
did not end up happening.

19:32.000 --> 19:33.500
So, I think that it's important
that you really

19:33.567 --> 19:35.867
review your contracts
before signing them.

19:35.934 --> 19:38.133
Yeah. [laughs]
I-I agree with you.

19:38.200 --> 19:41.967
I didn't actually think of force majeure,
but that's exactly what it is.

19:42.033 --> 19:44.233
It's a major force
that pre-- precludes

19:44.300 --> 19:47.600
either party from performing
the terms of the contract,

19:47.667 --> 19:51.133
and defining what their
responsibility is, if any,

19:51.200 --> 19:54.533
if something prevents
the contract from going forward.

19:54.600 --> 19:55.600
Interesting.

